Write a program that prompts the user for $4$ integers that represent time,
sets a boolean variable to true exactly when the time entered is valid, and
then prints the boolean variable. The $4$ integer values are as follows:
\begin{itemize}
  \li The first integer is $0$ if the time entered is in $12$--hour format; it
      is $1$ if the time entered is in $24$--hour format
  \li The second integer represents the hour. Note that in the $12$--hour
      format, the hour is valid if it is 
      \textred{from $1$ to  $12$ (inclusive)}; 
      in the
      $24$--hour format, the hour is valid if it is 
      \textred{from $0$ and $23$ (inclusive)}.
  \li The third integer represents the minute. 
  \li The fourth integer represents the second.
\end{itemize}

{\bf Test 1:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 -1 -5 -1}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 2:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 1 -5 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 3:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 1 70 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 4:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 1 7 244}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 5:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 0 7 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 6:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 0 13 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 7:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{0 1 7 2}
1
\end{console}

{\bf Test 8:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 1 -5 1}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 9:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 1 -5 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 10:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 1 70 2}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 11:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 1 7 244}
0
\end{console}

{\bf Test 12:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 0 7 2}
1
\end{console}

{\bf Test 13:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 0 13 2}
1
\end{console}

{\bf Test 14:}
\begin{console}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\underline{1 24 7 2}
0
\end{console}
